# Phase 2 Frontend Implementation Plan — Billing, Khata, Purchases & Polish

This plan covers Stages 4, 5, and 6 of Phase 2, building the complete frontend layers for **Billing** (customer invoicing), **Khata** (credit ledger), **Purchases** (supplier stock-in), **Expenses**, and overall **Polish** (item history tab, settings receipt, keyboard shortcuts).

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Print Layouts**: Receipts will be formatted using CSS `@media print` layout so standard paper rolls (thermal/A4) can be printed cleanly using native browser print (`window.print()`).
> - **Keyboard Shortcuts**: Global hooks will be bound to keys (`Ctrl+N`, `Ctrl+1-10`, `F2`, `Enter`, `Escape`) to allow high-speed retail checkout.
> - **State Persistence**: The local billing slots (up to 10 slots) will be managed via a Zustand store with localStorage persistence for crash/page-refresh recovery.

